},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13900,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/02\/wiping-turban-socks-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":25651,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping turbans and socks in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 2, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Mughirah ibn Shu\u2019bah reported: I was with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, on a journey and I reached out to take off his leather socks. The Prophet said, \u201cLeave them, for I have worn them in a state of purity.\u201d Then, the Prophet wiped over them for\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25662,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/21\/wipe-over-socks-headgear-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":25651,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Wiping over socks and headgear in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Bilal reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, wiped over leather socks and head coverings in ablution. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 275 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Ibn Taymiyyah said, \u201cSince it is permitted for men to wipe over clothing on the head, so is it\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25653,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/20\/wipe-non-leathe